MCI Communications Corp. said it will become Georgia-Pacific Corp. 's exclusive telecommunications provider, linking more than 390 Georgia-Pacific sites in the 

Terms of the three-year agreement weren't disclosed.
MCI said it will provide voice, data, facsimile, 800 and credit-card services, and will negotiate with telecommunications hardware makers and special-service providers on behalf of Georgia-Pacific. 

MCI won a smaller contract with Georgia-Pacific earlier this year. 

